Fly Boy INC main man Kizz Daniel is set to release his sophomore studio album soon. The Baba singer has shared provoking artwork and title. <img class="wp-image-703830 size-full alignnone lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/unnamed-2-4.jpg" alt="" width="882" height="882" /> The anticipated album is titled No Bad Songz. As the name implies, the album aims to make an impact following Daniel’s string of hit singles and collaborations. It is scheduled to hit stores in October. The album cover art was designed by celebrity photographer and graphic artist Amazing Klef.